      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/9b9a66888d16117a32aa30ea8a972fa22a4de1d5",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "be3640b0fae053ca45482bb4bcf5e4ed97b88614",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/be3640b0fae053ca45482bb4bcf5e4ed97b88614"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree be3640b0fae053ca45482bb4bcf5e4ed97b88614\nparent 9cad97f6cdf1bd660732cd10e844a6a7e0771ea0\nauthor sedited <seb.kung@gmail.com> 1769773684 +0100\ncommitter sedited <seb.kung@gmail.com> 1772282000 +0100\n\nvalidation: Move block into BlockConnected signal\n\nThis makes existing behaviour of the block's destructor triggering on\nthe scheduler thread more explicit by moving it to the thread.\n\nIt doing so is useful, since it does not block the main thread while\nreleasing memory. Ensure that the block's destructor is only triggered\nfrom the scheduler thread. Though it is possible that this only\ndecrements the reference count, blocks are also read from disk in\n`ConnectTip`, which now explicitly results in their memory being\nreleased outside the main thread.\n",
